sentences: Alexandra Ioana Stan (born 10 June 1989) is a Romanian singer-songwriter.
Born in the city of Constanța, she made her worldwide breakthrough with the 2010 single "Mr. Saxobeat", which was written and produced by Marcel Prodan and Andrei Nemirschi.
They had previously discovered Stan at a karaoke bar in 2009 and signed her to their label, Maan Records.
"Mr. Saxobeat" had followed the singer's debut single, "Lollipop (Param Pam Pam)" (2009), which brought her moderate fame in Romania.
Saxobeats, Stan's debut studio album, was released in August 2011 and features the follow-up singles "Get Back (ASAP)" (2011) and "Lemonade" (2012), which had moderate success in Europe.
